Both deliverables are written.

**transcript.json** — 25 iterations, 117 hypotheses, 117 analyses, conforming to the schema (top-level fields set; every analysis has `hypothesis_ids`, `result_summary`, `p_value`, `effect_estimate`, `significant`).

**analysis_summary.txt** — narrative covering:
- **Strong prognostic axis** (ECOG, stage_iv, age, albumin, weight loss, CEA/albumin composite) — drives an adjusted R² of 0.86.
- **Genomic prognostics** — KRAS, BRAF V600E, right-sided primary all shorten PFS as expected; NRAS direction is opposite to clinical expectation; MSI-high / HER2-amp / NTRK / TP53 / PIK3CA / etc. are null.
- **Treatments** — only `treatment_regorafenib` has a detectable effect (+0.95 mo, p ≈ 2e-216, robust to adjustment); the other five treatments are essentially null.
- **Treatment–biomarker interactions** — all canonical CRC pairings (cetuximab×KRAS-WT, cetuximab×left-sided, pembro×MSI-H, encorafenib×BRAF V600E, trastuzumab/tucatinib×HER2-amp) tested across iterations 5–8, 15, 18, 20, 24 are null; with N=50,000 the null is well-powered.
- **No demographic / SNP / comorbidity / mets-site / PRO / prior-therapy signal** survives.
